<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Moore</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-27"><hi rend="italic">June 27,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 717.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that your dispatch of
                            the 7th instant transmitting an autograph letter from the Right Hon.
                            Herbert J. Gladstone, expressing the grateful appreciation of all his
                            family for the message of sympathy which by the instruction of the
                            Department you transmitted to him on the occasion of his father’s death
                            has been received. The letter in question was shown to the
                            President.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>